United States of America, Western District of Washington} ss:

I hereby certify and return that I served the annexed Writ of Habeas Corpus on the therein named L.C. Smith, Sheriff of King County, Washington, by handing to and leaving a true copy thereof with Oscar Wise, Deputy Sheriff of King County Washington personally at Seattle in said District on the 1st day of July, A.D. 1905
C.B. Hopkins U.S. Marshal.
By Fred M. Laihe
Marshal's Fees Service $2.00 Mileage $0.12 $2.12
IN THE CIRCUIT COURT OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE NINTH CIRCUIT, WESTERN DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON.
In the Matter of the Application of L.J. Urann for a WRIT OF HABEAS CORPUS.
RETURN.
To the Honorable C.H. Hanford, Judge of the above entitled Court:

Come now L.C. Smith, sheriff of King county, Washington, and Morris Wolf, agent of the State of Massachusetts, upon whom were a served copies of a writ of habeas corpus in the above entitled matter, and in obedience to said writ make the following return and show to this honorable court:
That the petitioner L.J. Urann is now in the custody of L.C. Smith, sheriff of King county, Washington, and that the detention of said petitioner is lawful in this:

That said L.C. Smith, sheriff of King county, Washington acting in the public service and not otherwise, did, on the 1st day of July, 1905, take into custody the petitioner herein upon a warrant of arrest issued by Albert E. Mead, governor of the State of Washington, and directed to Morris Wolf, agent of the State of Massachusetts, wherein and whereby said Morris Wolf was directed to take the said L.J. Urann, wherever he might be found in the State of Washington, and transfer him to the line thereof and return him to the jurisdiction of the superior court of Suffolk County, Commonwealth of Massachusetts.
Hereto there is attached and made a part of this return a copy of said warrant of arrest issued by Elbert E. Mead, governor of the State of Washington.
Having shown to this honorable court that said petitioner L.J.

Urann is held by due and lawful process, your orators nevertheless now produce before this honorable court the body of L.J. Urann in compliance with the direction of writ of habeas corpus, and pray this honorable court that said writ be now denied, and that the petitioner may be held under said warrant issued by the governor of the State of Washington hereinabove referred to.
L.C. Smith Morris Wolf Respondents
STATE OF WASHINGTON, County of King.} ss.

L.C. SMITH and MORRIS WOLF, being first first duly sworn, each for himself, and not one for the other, says: That he is the respondent in the foregoing return; that he has read the same, knows the contents thereof, and believes the same to be.
L.C. Smith Morris Wolf
Subscribed and sworn to before me, this third day of July, 1905. Kenneth Mackeeboh Notary public in and for the State of Washington, residing at Seattle in said state.
UNITED STATES OF AMERICA. STATE OF WASHINGTON.
Executive Department.
TO ALL TO WHOM THESE PRESENTS SHALL COME GREETING:

WHEREAS, It has been represented to me by His Excellency WILLIAM L. DOUGLAS Governor of the State of Massachusetts that LOUIS L. URANN stands charged in said State with the crime of Larceny committed in the County of Suffolk in said state and is a fugitive from the justice of said State and has taken refuge in the State of Washington;

AND WHEREAS, the said Governor of the State of Massachusetts has pursuant to the constitution and laws of the United States demanded of me that I cause the said Louis J. Urann to be arrested and delivered to Morris Wolf, agent authorized to receivedhim into his custody and convey him back to said State of Massachusetts

AND WHEREAS, said representation and demand are accompanied by affidavits, indictments and warrant whereby the said Louis J. Urann is charged with the said crime and being a fugitive from the justice of said State and having taken refuge in the State of Washington, which are certified by said Governor of Massachusetts to be duly authenticated.

NOW THEREFORE, I, A.E. MEAD, Governor of the State of Washington, do hereby authorize and empower MORRIS WOLF the agent named in said demand to take the said Louis J. Urann wherever he may be found in this State, and transfer him to the line thereof at the expense of The State of Massachusetts.
And I hereby command all civil officers within the said State of Washington to afford alll needful assistance for the execution of this warrant.
IN TESTIMONY WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand and caused the Seal of the said State to be affixed at Olympia, this first day of July, A.D. 1905. (Signed) Albert E. Mead
(SEAL)
